quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  36,52,"They will say, "
  36,53,"It will not be but one blast, and at once they are all brought present before Us."
  36,54,"So today [i.e., the Day of Judgement] no soul will be wronged at all, and you will not be recompensed except for what you used to do."
  37,37,"Rather, he [i.e., the Prophet (ﷺ)] has come with the truth and confirmed the [previous] messengers."
  37,38,"Indeed, you [disbelievers] will be tasters of the painful punishment,"
  37,39,"And you will not be recompensed except for what you used to do -"
  38,16,"And they say, "
  38,17,"Be patient over what they say and remember Our servant, David, the possessor of strength; indeed, he was one who repeatedly turned back [to Allāh]."
  38,18,"Indeed, We subjected the mountains [to praise] with him, exalting [Allāh] in the [late] afternoon and [after] sunrise."
  39,1,"The revelation of the Book [i.e., the Qur’ān] is from Allāh, the Exalted in Might, the Wise."
  39,2,"Indeed, We have sent down to you the Book, [O Muḥammad], in truth. So worship Allāh, [being] sincere to Him in religion."
  39,3,"Unquestionably, for Allāh is the pure religion.{1} And those who take protectors besides Him [say], ",footnotes:1:[i.e., acceptable to Allāh is that none be associated with Him in worship and obedience.]
